{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f9313673-19f0-43ba-bf52-72f74768b5a5","content":"The most likely issue: **.NET MAUI's Android build tooling doesn't use `JAVA_HOME`** by default. It has its own JDK discovery, so your Temurin installation is being ignored.\n\n**Fix — pick one:**\n\n1. **Set `JavaSdkDirectory` in your `.csproj`:**\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <JavaSdkDirectory>/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/temurin-17.jdk/Contents/Home</JavaSdkDirectory>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n2. **Pass it on the command line:**\n   ```bash\n   dotnet build -p:JavaSdkDirectory=/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/temurin-17.jdk/Contents/Home\n   ```\n\n3. **Or install Microsoft's bundled JDK (recommended, auto-detected):**\n   ```bash\n   dotnet workload install maui\n   ```\n   This installs Microsoft OpenJDK 17 to a path the build system finds automatically.\n\n**Verify your path** — on macOS the `JAVA_HOME` (and `JavaSdkDirectory`) must end in `/Contents/Home`, not just the `.jdk` directory. Confirm with:\n```bash\nls $JAVA_HOME/bin/java\n```\n\nIf that doesn't resolve, share the exact error message and I can narrow it down further.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a87e125b-356d-45f5-950a-8b487fcc92ca","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory appears to be empty. Let me just answer the user's question based on my knowledge.\n\nThe most likely issue is that the .NET Android/MAUI build system on macOS doesn't automatically use `JAVA_HOME`. The build tools have their own JDK discovery mechanism, and you typically need to explicitly tell MSBuild where your JDK is.\n\nLet me provide a clear, concise answer.","outputTokens":440,"requestId":"6C10:2625AA:863ED3:8ED257:6A0AF63A"},"id":"4ce81d9a-fae2-4a8c-b962-e7e6b61a53ce","timestamp":"2026-05-18T11:21:41.219Z","parentId":"3dabeba1-ce79-4ae0-842c-0918844499d5"}
